label.value: L-dopa decarboxylase activator activity

definition.value: Interacts with and increases L-dopa decarboxylase activity.

label.value: peroxidase inhibitor activity

definition.value: Interacts with, and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a peroxidase.

label.value: nitric-oxide synthase inhibitor activity

definition.value: Interacts with, and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of nitric oxide synthase.

label.value: CHOP-C|EBP complex

definition.value: A heterodimeric protein complex that is composed of the transcription factor CHOP (GADD153) and a member of the C|EBP family of transcription factors.

label.value: netrin receptor activity involved in chemoattraction

definition.value: Combining with a netrin signal and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to contribute to the directed movement of a motile cell towards a higher concentration of netrin.

label.value: leptin receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with the fat-cell specific hormone leptin and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label.value: G-protein coupled olfactory receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with an odorant and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein -  promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label.value: signaling receptor activity

definition.value: Receiving a signal and transmitting the signal in the cell to initiate a change in cell activity. A signal is a physical entity or change in state that is used to transfer information in order to trigger a response.

label.value: cargo receptor activity

definition.value: Combining selectively with an extracellular macromolecule and delivering the macromolecule into the cell via endocytosis.

label.value: reelin receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with the secreted glycoprotein reelin, and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label.value: sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with the sphingolipid sphingosine-1-phosphate (S1P), and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein.

label.value: G-protein coupled receptor dimeric complex

definition.value: A protein complex that contains two G-protein coupled receptors.

label.value: G-protein coupled receptor homodimeric complex

definition.value: A protein complex that contains two G-protein coupled receptors (GPCRs) of the same subtype. Formation of a GPCR homodimer may be important for the transport of newly formed receptors to the cell surface, and the function of the receptor.

label.value: G-protein coupled receptor heterodimeric complex

definition.value: A protein complex that contains two G-protein coupled receptors (GPCRs) of different subtypes. Formation of a GPCR heterodimer may alter the functional property of the GPCR.

label.value: large latent transforming growth factor-beta complex

definition.value: A protein complex containing latency-associated proteins (LAPs), mature disulphide-linked dimeric TGF-beta, and latent TGF-beta binding proteins (LTBPs). TGF-beta is mostly secreted as part of the large latent complex, and must be subsequently released from the LLC in order to bind to cell surface receptors.

label.value: enkephalin receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with an enkephalin, and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein. A enkephalin is a pentapeptide (Tyr-Gly-Gly-Phe-Met or Tyr-Gly-Gly-Phe-Leu) involved in regulating nociception in the body.

label.value: morphine receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with morphine (17-methyl-7,8-didehydro-4,5alpha-epoxymorphinan-3,6alpha-diol), and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein.

label.value: dynorphin receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with a dynorphin peptide, and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein. Dynorphin is any opioid peptide that is generated by cleavage of the precursor protein prodynorphin.

label.value: ligand-activated RNA polymerase II transcription factor binding transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with a signal and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with an RNA polymerase II transcription factor, which may be a single protein or a complex, in order to modulate transcription. For example, some steroid hormone receptors bind to transcription factor complexes to regulate transcription of genes whose promoters do not contain hormone response elements.

label.value: glucocorticoid-activated sequence-specific DNA binding RNA polymerase II transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with a glucocorticoid and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.

label.value: glucocorticoid-activated RNA polymerase II transcription factor binding transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with a glucocorticoid and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with an RNA polymerase II transcription factor, which may be a single protein or a complex, in order to modulate transcription. For example, glucocorticoid-bound receptors can bind to transcription factor complexes to regulate transcription of genes whose promoters do not contain glucocorticoid response elements.

label.value: estrogen-activated sequence-specific DNA binding RNA polymerase II transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with estrogen and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.

label.value: estrogen-activated RNA polymerase II transcription factor binding transcription factor activity

definition.value: Combining with estrogen and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with an RNA polymerase II transcription factor, which may be a single protein or a complex, in order to modulate transcription. For example, estrogen-bound receptors can bind to transcription factor complexes to regulate transcription of genes whose promoters do not contain estrogen response elements.

label.value: G-protein coupled estrogen receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with estrogen and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein -  promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label.value: negative regulation of BMP signaling pathway by negative regulation of BMP secretion

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the BMP signaling pathway by stopping, preventing or reducing the frequency, rate or extent of secretion of a member of the BMP family of proteins from the signaling cell.

label.value: TNFSF11 binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 11 (TNFSF11), a member of the tumor necrosis factor (TNF) cytokine family.

label.value: TNFSF11 receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with a tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 11 (TNFSF11) and transmitting the signal across the cell membrane to initiate a change in cell activity or function.

label.value: IKKalpha-IKKalpha complex

definition.value: A homodimeric protein complex containing two IkappaB kinase (IKK) alpha subunits.

label.value: protein tyrosine kinase collagen receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with collagen and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity by catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein-L-tyrosine -eq- ADP + a protein-L-tyrosine phosphate.

label.value: collagen receptor activity

definition.value: Combining with a collagen and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label.value: MAP kinase activity involved in cell wall organization or biogenesis

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  protein + ATP -eq- protein phosphate + ADP by a mitogen-activated protein kinase, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to cell wall organization or biogenesis.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase activity involved in cell wall organization or biogenesis

definition.value: Catalysis of the concomitant phosphorylation of threonine (T) and tyrosine (Y) residues in a Thr-Glu-Tyr (TEY) thiolester sequence in a MAP kinase (MAPK) substrate, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to cell wall organization or biogenesis.

label.value: MAP kinase phosphatase activity involved in regulation of cell wall biogenesis

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphorylated MAP kinase + H2O -eq- a MAP kinase + phosphate, where the MAP kinase (MAPK) is part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to cell wall biogenesis.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase kinase activity involved in cell wall organization or biogenesis

definition.value: Catalysis of the phosphorylation and activation of a MAP kinase kinase (MAPKK), as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to cell wall organization or biogenesis.

label.value: MAP kinase activity involved in conjugation with cellular fusion

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  protein + ATP -eq- protein phosphate + ADP by a mitogen-activated protein kinase, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to conjugation with cellular fusion.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase activity involved in conjugation with cellular fusion

definition.value: Catalysis of the concomitant phosphorylation of threonine (T) and tyrosine (Y) residues in a Thr-Glu-Tyr (TEY) thiolester sequence in a MAP kinase (MAPK) substrate, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to conjugation with cellular fusion.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase kinase activity involved in conjugation with cellular fusion

definition.value: Catalysis of the phosphorylation and activation of a MAP kinase kinase (MAPKK), as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to cell wall biogenesis.

label.value: MAP kinase phosphatase activity involved in regulation of conjugation with cellular fusion

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphorylated MAP kinase + H2O -eq- a MAP kinase + phosphate, where the MAP kinase (MAPK) is part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to conjugation with cellular fusion.

label.value: MAP kinase activity involved in innate immune response

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  protein + ATP -eq- protein phosphate + ADP by a mitogen-activated protein kinase, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to an innate immune response.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase activity involved in innate immune response

definition.value: Catalysis of the concomitant phosphorylation of threonine (T) and tyrosine (Y) residues in a Thr-Glu-Tyr (TEY) thiolester sequence in a MAP kinase (MAPK) substrate, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to an innate immune response.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase kinase activity involved in innate immune response

definition.value: Catalysis of the phosphorylation and activation of a MAP kinase kinase (MAPKK), as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to an innate immune response.

label.value: MAP kinase phosphatase activity involved in regulation of innate immune response

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphorylated MAP kinase + H2O -eq- a MAP kinase + phosphate, where the MAP kinase (MAPK) is part of a MAPK signaling cascade that contributes to an innate immune response.

label.value: MAP kinase activity involved in osmosensory signaling pathway

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  protein + ATP -eq- protein phosphate + ADP by a mitogen-activated protein kinase, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that passes on a signal within an osmosensory signaling pathway.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase activity involved in osmosensory signaling pathway

definition.value: Catalysis of the concomitant phosphorylation of threonine (T) and tyrosine (Y) residues in a Thr-Glu-Tyr (TEY) thiolester sequence in a MAP kinase (MAPK) substrate, as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that passes on a signal within an osmosensory signaling pathway.

label.value: MAP kinase kinase kinase activity involved in osmosensory signaling pathway

definition.value: Catalysis of the phosphorylation and activation of a MAP kinase kinase (MAPKK), as part of a MAPK signaling cascade that passes on a signal within an osmosensory signaling pathway.

label.value: MAP kinase phosphatase activity involved in regulation of osmosensory signaling pathway

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphorylated MAP kinase + H2O -eq- a MAP kinase + phosphate, where the MAP kinase (MAPK) is part of a MAPK signaling cascade that passes on a signal within an osmosensory signaling pathway.

label.value: vascular endothelial growth factor binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a vascular endothelial growth factor.

label.value: sequestering of BMP from receptor via BMP binding

definition.value: Binding to a bone morphogenetic protein (BMP) in the extracellular region, and inhibiting BMP signaling by preventing BMP from binding to its cell surface receptor.

label.value: nodal binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a nodal protein, a member of the transforming growth factor-beta superfamily.

label.value: activin receptor antagonist activity

definition.value: Interacting with an activin receptor complex to reduce the action of another ligand, the agonist. A receptor antagonist does not initiate signaling upon binding to a receptor, but instead blocks an agonist from binding to the receptor.
